 A recent survey by the British Heart Foundation showed two fifths of parents are badgered by their children each week to buy food after seeing it advertised on TV , prompting the charity to deliver a 30,000 strong petition asking the Government to ban junk food adverts being shown before the 9 pm watershed .
A recent British Heart and survey quizzed more than 2,000 parents with children under the age of 16 .
Seven in ten parents are exposed to more TV advertising for unhealthy products .